          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-3-1618925230138-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Cut the <strong>cherry tomatoes</strong> in half</p><p>Add the<strong> cider vinegar </strong>to a large bowl with 2 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[4 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil </strong>and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>– this is your<strong> dressing</strong></p><p>Set both aside for serving</p><p>Once the onion has caramelised, add 1 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tbsp]</span><strong> flour</strong> and cook for 30 secs, then add 2 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [4 tbsp] </span><strong>milk </strong>and cook for a further 30 secs or until a thick paste has formed – this is your <strong>onion mixture </strong></p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1618925256465-x200.jpg",
